sect1.para:
It is also possible to cut the model using cleavages (see 
	)	if one wishes to limit the visible part by planes others than those corresponding
	to a constant value of a coordinate.

Each define cleavage will hide the chosen number of planes beginning from the greatest value
	for hx + ky + lz that is present in the model. To remove planes from the other side of the model,
	signs of h, k and l must be reversed.
